# Language statistics (GitHub Linguist)
#
# The repo has two tracks (see CLAUDE.md / README): the native Swift/SwiftUI
# macOS & iOS apps under native/ are the PRIMARY product; the Docker/FastAPI
# web app under legacy-docker/ is DEPRECATED and kept for reference only.
#
# By default Linguist counts every file, so the deprecated Python/JS/CSS web
# app (~179 .py + all .js/.css) dominates the sidebar breakdown and buries
# Swift. Mark the legacy track as vendored so it is excluded from the language
# stats and Swift ranks first, matching what the project actually is.
legacy-docker/** linguist-vendored
